# Define age groups
bins = [0, 18, 35, 50, 65, 100]
labels = ['0-18', '19-35', '36-50', '51-65', '66+']

# Create a new column for age groups
df['AgeGroup'] = pd.cut(df['Age'], bins=bins, labels=labels, right=False)

# Group by Gender and AgeGroup and count the number of patients
distribution = df.groupby(['Gender', 'AgeGroup']).size().unstack(fill_value=0)

# Print the distribution
print(distribution)

# Convert date columns to datetime
df['ScheduledDay'] = pd.to_datetime(df['ScheduledDay'])
df['AppointmentDay'] = pd.to_datetime(df['AppointmentDay'])

# Calculate days difference
df['DaysDifference'] = (df['AppointmentDay'] - df['ScheduledDay']).dt.days

# Compute the average waiting time by neighborhood
avg_days_by_neighborhood = df.groupby('Neighbourhood')['DaysDifference'].mean().sort_values(ascending=False)

# Select the top 10 neighborhoods with the longest waiting time
top_10_neighborhoods = avg_days_by_neighborhood.head(10)

# Create a DataFrame for the heatmap
heatmap_data = pd.DataFrame(top_10_neighborhoods)

# Plot the heatmap
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.heatmap(heatmap_data, cmap="coolwarm", annot=True, fmt=".1f", linewidths=0.5, cbar=True)

# Titles and labels
plt.title("Top 10 Neighborhoods with the Longest Waiting Time")
plt.xlabel("Average Waiting Time (Days)")
plt.ylabel("Neighborhood")

# Show the plot
plt.show()

# Convert 'ScheduledDay' to datetime
df['ScheduledDay'] = pd.to_datetime(df['ScheduledDay'])

# Extract day of the week as integers (0=Monday, 6=Sunday)
df['DayOfWeek'] = df['ScheduledDay'].dt.dayofweek

# Map integers to day names
day_names = {
    0: 'Monday',
    1: 'Tuesday',
    2: 'Wednesday',
    3: 'Thursday',
    4: 'Friday',
    5: 'Saturday',
    6: 'Sunday'
}
df['DayOfWeek'] = df['DayOfWeek'].map(day_names)

# Verify the 'DayOfWeek' column
print(df['DayOfWeek'].head())

# Count weekend appointments (Saturday and Sunday)
weekend_appointments = df[df['DayOfWeek'].isin(['Saturday', 'Sunday'])].shape[0]
total_appointments = df.shape[0]
weekend_percentage = (weekend_appointments / total_appointments) * 100

print(f"Appointments scheduled on weekends: {weekend_appointments}")
print(f"Percentage of total appointments: {weekend_percentage:.2f}%")

6. No Show Rate on Weekdays vs. Weekends¶
In [86]:
# Convert 'AppointmentDay' to datetime
df['AppointmentDay'] = pd.to_datetime(df['AppointmentDay'])

# Extract the day of the week (0 = Monday, 6 = Sunday)
df['DayOfWeek'] = df['AppointmentDay'].dt.dayofweek

# Classify days as Weekday or Weekend
df['DayType'] = df['DayOfWeek'].apply(lambda x: 'Weekend' if x >= 5 else 'Weekday')

# Check unique values in 'Showed_up'
print("Unique values in 'Showed_up':", df['Showed_up'].unique())

# Calculate no-show rate for Weekdays and Weekends
if df['Showed_up'].dtype == 'object':  # If 'Showed_up' contains 'Yes'/'No'
    no_show_rate = df.groupby('DayType')['Showed_up'].apply(lambda x: (x == 'No').mean())
else:  # If 'Showed_up' contains True/False
    no_show_rate = df.groupby('DayType')['Showed_up'].apply(lambda x: (x == False).mean())

# Print the no-show rate
print("No-Show Rate:")
print(no_show_rate)

# Verify distribution of appointments by DayType
print("\nAppointment Distribution by DayType:")
print(df['DayType'].value_counts())

8. No-Show Rate by Health Condition¶
In [90]:
# List of health conditions to analyze
health_conditions = ['Hipertension', 'Diabetes', 'Alcoholism', 'Handcap']

# Function to calculate no-show rate for multiple conditions
def no_show_rate_by_health_condition(df, conditions):
    rates = {}
    for condition in conditions:
        rates[condition] = df.groupby(condition)['Showed_up'].apply(lambda x: (x == False).mean() * 100)
    return rates

# Calculate no-show rates
no_show_rates = no_show_rate_by_health_condition(df, health_conditions)

# Print results
for condition, rate in no_show_rates.items():
    print(f"\nNo-show rate for {condition}:\n", rate)
